text: Tensors used machine deep learning multi-dimensional array structures. addition space efficient provide common framework automatic differentiation, engine deep neural network training. packages, notably R interfaces tensorflow keras, use native R structures tensor storage, form vectors (1-dimentional arrays), matrices (2 dimensions), higher dimensional arrays. Tensors usually represent “set ” relationships. example, vector like point <- c(20.2, 19.1, 24.8) might represent 1-dimensional tensor storing point space X, Y, Z coordinate values. matrix form points <- matrix(runif(10*3), ncol = 3, nrow = 10) represent 10 points, points[6, ] accessing sixth. However, tensors often referred “dimensionality” avoid confusing array dimensions data dimensions; rather, ’d call point (1-d array) “rank 1 tensor” matrix points (2-d array) “rank 2 tensor”. hand, common refer specific “dimensions” array “axes” (Python’s numpy refers axes multidimensional arrays example). TidyTensor eschews well favor rank-based nomenclature; rather referring first second axes points (slicing data point spatial coordinate respectively), ’ll refer first second ranks. Tensors also shape, conveniently returned R’s dim() function. point tensor shape (3) (parentheses used denote shape vector) points shape (10, 3). Lastly, “margins” frequently used refer individual ranks/axes R functions apply().
